  {num:50,ctx:`Bright Star Pvt. Ltd., a regular GST registered supplier of both taxable and exempted goods, is located in Shimla, Himachal Pradesh. The company provides the following details: (i) The aggregate turnover (all intra-State) of goods exceeded ' 20 lakh on 29th July 2025 and ' 40 lakh on 16th August 2025. It submitted the application for GST registration on 30th August, 2025. The registration certificate is granted to it on 8th September 2025. (ii) It also entered into a contract with Zenith Ltd. of Manali, Himachal Pradesh on 10th September 2025 for the supply of taxable goods worth ' 15 lakh. The payment for the same was received on 12th September 2025. The goods were scheduled for delivery on 25th September, 2025 but were removed from the factory on 24th September, 2025. (iii) It has opted monthly filing of GSTR 3B return and filed GSTR 3B return for the month of September, 2025 on 19th December 2025. The prescribed due date to file the said GSTR 3B return was 20th October, 2025. The amount of net GST payable in cash on supplies made for said September month work out to be 56,000 which was paid on 19th December, 2025. Based on the above information, choose the correct answer for the questions 1 to 3.`,qs:[
